= section "The Subjunctive Mood" do
  %p The Novegradian subjunctive is an analytic construction formed from the past tense L- form of a verb and a special form of буити “be”, a fossilized aorist. Only three aorist forms remain: the singular, dual, and plural. As with the past tense and future hypthetical, the L-form verb agrees in gender and number with its subject. With цидати “read” (and a masculine subject):
