  %p Verbs with vocalizing /j/ take the ending #{t "-ей", "-ei"} in the second person forms rather than -и- or -ѣ-. In the first person forms, the expected -ѣ- appears, but with a /j/ glide. For #{t "пити", "píti"} “drink”: #{t "пей", "péi"}, #{t "пейта", "péita"}, #{t "пейте", "péite"}, #{t "пиѣута", "piě́uta"}, #{t "пиѣмте", "piě́mte"}.
